{"questionId":"27669","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>cos</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find the coordinates of the points on the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid attempt to solve their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>At least 2 correct <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinates (may be seen in coordinates)&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Accept additional correct solutions outside the domain.<br>Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> if any additional incorrect solutions are given.</p>\n<p><br>correct coordinates (may be seen in graph for part (c))&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award a maximum of <em><strong>M1A1A1A1A0</strong></em> if any additional solutions are given.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If candidates do not find at least two correct <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinates, it is possible to award the appropriate final marks for their correct coordinates, such as <strong>M1A0A0A1A0</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27669","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.10b.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence find the coordinates of the points on the graph of y=f(x) where f'x=0.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}